<COMPANIES></COMPANIES>
<UNKNOWN></UNKNOWN>
<TEXT>
<TITLE></TITLE>
<DATELINE></DATELINE>
<BODY>Stalin led the Soviet Union through its post-war reconstruction phase, which saw a significant rise in tension with the Western world that would later be known as the Cold War. During this period, the USSR became the second country in the world to successfully develop a nuclear weapon, as well as launching the Great Plan for the Transformation of Nature in response to another widespread famine and the Great Construction Projects of Communism.</BODY>
</TEXT>
</REUTERS>

<REUTERS>
<DATE></DATE>
<TOPICS></TOPICS>
<PLACES></PLACES>
