<UNKNOWN></UNKNOWN>
<TEXT>
<TITLE></TITLE>
<DATELINE></DATELINE>
<BODY>Stalin played a decisive role in engineering the 1921 Red Army invasion of Georgia, following which he adopted particularly hardline, centralist policies towards Soviet Georgia. This led to the Georgian Affair of 1922 and other repressions.[18][19] Stalin's actions in Georgia created a rift with Lenin, who believed that all the Soviet states should stand equal.</BODY>
</TEXT>
</REUTERS>

