<DATELINE></DATELINE>
<BODY>The eastern part of Poland, Latvia, Estonia, Finland and part of Romania were recognized as parts of the Soviet sphere of influence,[144] with Lithuania added in a second secret protocol in September 1939.[145] Stalin and Ribbentrop traded toasts on the night of the signing discussing past hostilities between the countries.</BODY>
</TEXT>
