<UNKNOWN></UNKNOWN>
<TEXT>
<TITLE></TITLE>
<DATELINE></DATELINE>
<BODY>After Stalin declared that he was going to "solve the Baltic problem", by June 1940, Lithuania, Latvia and Estonia were merged into the Soviet Union, after repressions and actions therein brought about the deaths of over 160,000 citizens of these states.</BODY>
</TEXT>
</REUTERS>

