<UNKNOWN></UNKNOWN>
<TEXT>
<TITLE></TITLE>
<DATELINE></DATELINE>
<BODY>After this campaign, Stalin took actions to bolster the Soviet military, modify training and improve propaganda efforts in the Soviet military.[154] In June 1940, Stalin directed the Soviet annexation of Bessarabia and northern Bukovina, proclaiming this formerly Romanian territory part of the Moldavian Soviet Socialist Republic. But in annexing northern Bukovina, Stalin had gone beyond the agreed limits of the secret protocol.</BODY>
</TEXT>
</REUTERS>

