<TEXT>
<TITLE></TITLE>
<DATELINE></DATELINE>
<BODY> Although Stalin had received warnings from spies and his generals, he felt that Germany would not attack the Soviet Union until Germany had defeated Britain. In the initial hours after the German attack commenced, Stalin hesitated, wanting to ensure that the German attack was sanctioned by Hitler, rather than the unauthorized action of a rogue general.</BODY>
</TEXT>
